  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;Prior to the first occupation of the development hereby approved a minimum of 1 Swift nesting bricks and/or boxes shall be provided at or close to eaves level of the development hereby approved. The bricks/boxes shall be retained thereafter in perpetuity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;REASON: In order to promote biodiversity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "<p>The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nREASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p><p>\r\n</p>",
    "<p>The Development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.\r\n</p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;All new external facing and roofing materials in respect of all the works hereby approved shall match those of the existing building in respect of materials used, detailed execution and finished appearance including type, size, colour, profile and texture.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\r\n\r\nREASON: In order to preserve the appearance of the host building, wider terrace, and the Queensbridge Road Conservation Area.&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;Prior to the commencement of the relevant part of works, detailed elevation and section drawings at a scale of 1:20 and/or 1:50 shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, the details shall show the materials used, the glazing thickness and specifications, and the proposed design of the side rooflight.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON: In order to preserve the appearance of the host property, terrace, wider streetscene and Queensbridge Road Conservation Area.&lt;/p&gt;"
